quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  98,8,"Their recompense lies with their Lord: Gardens of eternity beneath which rivers flow; therein they shall dwell, forever and ever. Allah is well-pleased with them, and they are well-pleased with Him. All this is for him who fears his Lord."{1},footnotes:1:1
  99,1,"When the earth will be shaken with a mighty shaking,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  99,2,"and the earth will throw up all her burdens,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  99,3,"and man will cry out: “What is the matter with her?”"{1},footnotes:1:1
  99,4,"On that Day it will relate all her news,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  99,5,"for your Lord will have commanded her (to do so)."
  99,6,"On that Day people will go forth in varying states so that they be shown their deeds."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  99,7,"So, whoever does an atom's weight of good shall see it;"
  99,8,"and whoever does an atom's weight of evil shall see it."{1},footnotes:1:1
  100,1,"By (the horses) that charge snorting,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  100,2,"then raise sparks of fire (by their hoofs),"{1},footnotes:1:1
  100,3,"then raid by the dawn,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  100,4,"and blaze a trail of dust,"
  100,5,"and penetrate deep into a host."
  100,6,"Verily man is most ungrateful to his Lord;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  100,7,"and he himself is a witness to that,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  100,8,"and surely he loves riches with a passionate loving."{1},footnotes:1:1
  100,9,"Is he not aware that when whatever lies (buried) in the graves is overthrown;"{1},footnotes:1:1